  - OSHA: Manufacturing and industrial facilities experience 2.1 million workplace injuries annually (BLS data)
  - Bureau of Labor Statistics: Manufacturing sector workplace fatality rate is 3.3 per 100,000 workers
  - ASIS International: Industrial facilities report 40%+ of security incidents occur at perimeter access points
  - Department of Energy: Critical industrial infrastructure faces increasing physical and cyber security threats
  - National Safety Council: Workplace violence costs US employers $130 billion annually across all industries
  - NFPA: Industrial fires cause an estimated $1.2 billion in direct property damage annually
  - Bureau of Labor Statistics: Manufacturing employs 12.9 million workers in the US
-->

<VerticalPage
